            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ Best thanks, dear Miss Stirling, for sending me such a nice picture of yours ¶  It is as if [I] ¶  saw you personally, which pleasure I shall doubtless have some day. Let your brothers get you with...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.00.00i</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Amie Stirling</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. For the text given here, see the image of the letter published in A. Stirling (1980), p. 27. Stirling collected plants for M in the 1890s, when she was a young girl (cf. M to A. Stirling, 15 November 1892); the earliest dated specimen at MEL is 1891 when she would have been 11 years old, and M's letter is therefore dated to 1891 as the earliest likely date it would have been written.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best thanks, dear Miss Stirling, for sending me such a nice picture of yours<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yourself<seg style="">? Word as transcribed ends at the extreme edge of the printed image and a continuation may have been cut off in the reproduction.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> It is as if [I]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg> — word omitted by M.</p>
               </note> saw you personally, which pleasure I shall doubtless have some day. Let your brothers get you with a rake all the floating waterweeds there also.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
